<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="933" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d933">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 814.48/9a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                President <persName type="to">Cabrera</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The White House</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-28">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 28, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In the great affliction with which you are now visited let me express on
                            my own behalf and on behalf of the people of the United States, the
                            fullest measure of sympathy. If there is any way in which we can be of
                            assistance to you in your trouble or in which we may alleviate some of
                            the sorrow and suffering you will experience because of the calamity, we
                            stand ready to do so. Until it is possible to render some material
                            assistance pray convey to the people of your country the sympathy which
                            we feel for them in the circumstances, a sympathy more profound by
                            reason of the proximities of our countries and the relation of our
                            people with yours.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>